.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pirates are cool!</span><hr size=1> Spelljammer was my favorite campaign setting.<br>
<br>
I know it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>sounds</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> sci-fi... D&amp;D in space and all...<br>
<br>
in practice though it was very much a fantasy setting, and steeped in political intrigue to boot.  <br>
<br>
It's the only D&amp;D campaign setting I know of that really portrays elves as the power hungry racists we all know they are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   They don't crave power for power's sake, but more like they felt they were the only ones intelligent enough to use it responsibly, and would thus kill anyone who got in their way of acquiring it.<br>
<br>
Plus they bring back orcs as real adversaries... intelligent militant bastards.<br>
<br>
And beholders...eep.<br>
<br>
And mindflayers... AAAAH.<br>
<br>
And neogi and their damned umberhulks... run away, run away!<br>
<br>
Mmmm, good good campaign setting.<br>
<br>
Delicious even.<br>
<br>
The ship to ship combat system was pretty good, and we had many a night locked in battle with some enemy vessel.  Owning a ship also helped solidify the party as a unit, because w/o a ship you're stuck as far as adventuring goes, so everyone would die to protect it, and we'd all use our hunting treasures to upgrade her weapons and hire on new crew to man the ballistae etc.<br>
<br>
Speaking of ballistae... I had a priest of celestian who took a critical hit from one... I pretty much won any &amp; every scar comparison contest after that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So anyways, I know it sounds sci-fi, but it's not, at all.  In fact, it's got a fantasy based physics set, so there's all kinds of stupid stuff you can do that would make no-sense whatsoever in a sci-fi setting.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=larraquemeleagrance>Larraque Meleagrance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Radical Dreamer</span><br>  Posts: 1651<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/8/03 4:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1729.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pirates are cool!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Tropico 2: Pirate Cove is probably the newest piratical computer game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
